WEBVTT

00:01.543 --> 00:03.629
Previously on
"Promised Land"...

00:03.629 --> 00:05.839
We have a history, Billy.
And now we're playing with fire.

00:05.839 --> 00:07.007
You're meant for more.

00:07.007 --> 00:08.050
Like what?

00:08.050 --> 00:09.593
Dinner, with me.

00:10.719 --> 00:15.307
[ Conversing in Spanish ]

00:15.307 --> 00:17.226
Lettie,
you remember this --

00:17.226 --> 00:19.228
we share our own secret.

00:19.228 --> 00:21.522
No!
[ Girls screaming ]

00:21.522 --> 00:24.233
If you try to take me down,
I won't go down alone.

00:24.233 --> 00:26.944
Antonio:
Bones in the vineyard...

00:26.944 --> 00:28.445
It was your father.

00:31.740 --> 00:33.742
[ Owl hoots ]

00:33.742 --> 00:36.119
[ Humming ]

00:40.457 --> 00:42.543
[ Girls screaming ]

00:42.543 --> 00:45.546
Manuel: Shh! Shh!

00:45.546 --> 00:47.005
[ Gunshot ]

00:47.005 --> 00:48.715
Unh!
[ Body thuds ]

00:48.715 --> 00:50.467
[ Groans ]

00:50.467 --> 00:52.427
♪♪

00:52.427 --> 00:54.471
[ Speaks Spanish ]

00:54.471 --> 00:56.598
Young Lettie: Margaret, we
have to stop the bleeding now!

00:57.808 --> 01:00.143
[ Groaning ]

01:02.771 --> 01:05.732
[ Sobs ] Marta...

01:05.732 --> 01:08.485
Margaret, give me something
to stop the blood. Hurry!

01:24.626 --> 01:26.503
Manuel?

01:28.338 --> 01:32.593
♪♪

01:32.593 --> 01:34.469
We have to
call the police.

01:34.469 --> 01:36.847
No.
We'll be arrested.

01:36.847 --> 01:38.223
He's the one who broke in,
Margaret.

01:38.223 --> 01:39.558
Do you want
to tell Billy?

01:41.143 --> 01:42.603
Or Joe?

01:42.603 --> 01:45.439
♪♪

01:45.439 --> 01:47.316
Then what do we do?

01:49.234 --> 01:52.112
We take him out
to the vineyard, bury him,

01:52.112 --> 01:54.531
get showered,
and put smiles on our faces.

01:54.531 --> 02:00.412
♪♪

02:00.412 --> 02:02.164
We'll take this
to our graves.

02:02.164 --> 02:06.543
♪♪

02:06.543 --> 02:08.712
[ Bird screeches ]

02:08.712 --> 02:13.342
♪♪

02:13.342 --> 02:15.719
You tossed and turned
all night.

02:17.346 --> 02:19.514
You did, too.

02:19.514 --> 02:21.975
You always get like that
before the harvest.

02:21.975 --> 02:23.852
No, it's not that
this time.

02:23.852 --> 02:25.646
I need to talk to Billy.
Have you seen him?

02:25.646 --> 02:27.105
Oh, Joe.

02:27.105 --> 02:28.565
Billy left.

02:28.565 --> 02:30.817
What do you mean, he left?
He left.

02:30.817 --> 02:32.986
Father Collins doesn't know
where he went.

02:32.986 --> 02:34.613
Doesn't make any sense.
Why would he leave?

02:38.325 --> 02:39.576
What's going on?

02:39.576 --> 02:41.870
Have you heard
about the bones?

02:41.870 --> 02:43.121
Oh, no, don't tell me.

02:43.121 --> 02:44.915
Those old rumors
about Honeycroft.

02:44.915 --> 02:47.042
Not again, please.
No, not Honeycroft.

02:47.042 --> 02:49.002
Javier
found a buried body

02:49.002 --> 02:51.213
out on the eastern edge
of the vineyard.

02:51.213 --> 02:54.049
I tested it.

02:54.049 --> 02:55.717
It was my father.

02:57.094 --> 02:59.054
How is that possible?

02:59.054 --> 03:01.056
I don't know.

03:01.056 --> 03:02.349
The last time
I talked to him,

03:02.349 --> 03:05.727
I told him I never wanted
to see him again.

03:05.727 --> 03:07.729
All these years,
I tortured myself

03:07.729 --> 03:10.774
for tearing
our family apart.

03:10.774 --> 03:12.943
Turns out
he was dead all along,

03:12.943 --> 03:14.945
not a mile
from where I slept.

03:14.945 --> 03:16.488
Oh, Joe.

03:20.701 --> 03:22.703
I am so sorry.

03:25.288 --> 03:28.375
A-At least
now you can move on.

03:28.375 --> 03:31.086
Move on? No, Lettie.

03:31.086 --> 03:34.339
I want to find out
who killed my father.

03:44.766 --> 03:47.936
[ Conversing in Spanish ]

03:47.936 --> 03:49.271
[ Laughs ]

04:46.161 --> 04:48.705
♪♪

04:59.966 --> 05:01.927
[ Laughter ]

05:11.478 --> 05:14.481
♪♪

05:19.569 --> 05:22.823
Oh! You, uh,
always sneak out

05:22.823 --> 05:24.074
before they're
out of the shower?

05:24.074 --> 05:25.575
I would have texted.

05:25.575 --> 05:27.911
You really know
how to treat a girl, huh?

05:27.911 --> 05:30.413
Empowered sexuality.
No strings.

05:30.413 --> 05:31.706
Just honesty.

05:31.706 --> 05:33.917
No one needs to end up
in a year-long dead end.

05:33.917 --> 05:35.502
Mm.
But usually, you know,
I'm the one

05:35.502 --> 05:37.671
that has to explain
the fourth-wave feminism.

05:37.671 --> 05:39.673
May have met your match.
Yeah.

05:39.673 --> 05:41.800
Relationships don't really
do it for me.

05:41.800 --> 05:42.884
What does?

05:42.884 --> 05:44.094
Work.

05:44.094 --> 05:46.596
Work makes you shiver?

05:46.596 --> 05:48.306
It does.
Good.

05:50.475 --> 05:53.895
I actually do have a question.
About the business.

05:53.895 --> 05:55.689
Ah. This a billable hour?
[ Chuckles ]

05:55.689 --> 05:57.440
I'm kidding.
Talk to me.

05:57.440 --> 05:59.609
We sold out another batch
of the sangria.

05:59.609 --> 06:01.528
You know the restaurant group
El Horno?
Yeah.

06:01.528 --> 06:04.698
Well, Gitana Sangria is their
fastest-selling adult beverage.

06:04.698 --> 06:06.283
Right.
We have an amazing product.

06:06.283 --> 06:07.450
What's the problem?

06:07.450 --> 06:09.661
It's not what. Who.

06:09.661 --> 06:14.666
My stepbrother/
business partner/grump

06:14.666 --> 06:17.752
who hates everything, Mateo,
is the problem.

06:17.752 --> 06:19.504
He wants Gitana
to fly under the radar,

06:19.504 --> 06:21.214
not to be traceable
back to him.

06:21.214 --> 06:23.925
Okay. You know what?
You leave him to me.

06:23.925 --> 06:25.552
But you...
But me?

06:25.552 --> 06:27.596
You don't get to leave yet.
But me?

06:27.596 --> 06:29.180
No, you're not leaving me yet.
Mnh-mnh.

06:29.180 --> 06:30.265
Oh, yeah?

06:30.265 --> 06:32.058
♪♪

06:32.058 --> 06:33.560
[ Sighs ] Good.
I caught you.

06:33.560 --> 06:36.229
Marta, did you tell him?
Tell me what?

06:36.229 --> 06:39.900
♪♪

06:39.900 --> 06:42.652
Father Ramos left Sonoma.

06:42.652 --> 06:44.321
What do you mean?
Like, left left?

06:44.321 --> 06:45.405
Yeah.

06:45.405 --> 06:46.823
Well, maybe
he'll come back.

06:46.823 --> 06:48.825
Don't hold your breath.
Last time, it took him 20 years.

06:48.825 --> 06:52.329
He didn't even say anything.
You okay?

06:52.329 --> 06:53.913
You know what? Yeah.

06:53.913 --> 06:55.915
Yeah, the first time he left,
it left an open wound,

06:55.915 --> 06:57.500
but these past few weeks,
reconnecting,

06:57.500 --> 06:59.711
I realized his shortcomings
weren't mine.

06:59.711 --> 07:01.421
How about you? I know he was
helping you with the...?

07:01.421 --> 07:03.590
Yeah. Yeah.

07:03.590 --> 07:05.425
Ramos taught me that
the first rule of sobriety

07:05.425 --> 07:07.719
is that no one
does it for you.

07:07.719 --> 07:10.347
So...I'll be fine.

07:10.347 --> 07:12.891
Marta, how is she?
How's who?

07:12.891 --> 07:15.810
Ow.
Lettie.
Billy left.

07:15.810 --> 07:17.312
[ Door closes ]

07:17.312 --> 07:18.938
Is she okay?

07:18.938 --> 07:22.609
Hey, booty call!
Get in here.

07:22.609 --> 07:23.693
How hot?

07:23.693 --> 07:25.320
Carmen:
How presumptuous.

07:25.320 --> 07:27.197
Maybe I was at an early
marketing meeting.

07:28.406 --> 07:30.283
[ Hushed ] Very hot.

07:30.283 --> 07:31.409
What's going on?

07:31.409 --> 07:33.495
Ramos left town.

07:33.495 --> 07:35.538
What? No way.

07:35.538 --> 07:37.791
How's Lettie?

07:37.791 --> 07:41.544
♪♪

07:41.544 --> 07:43.004
Hey, what does it say
about Joe and Lettie's marriage

07:43.004 --> 07:45.590
that Ramos leaves town and the
first thing we all do is ask,

07:45.590 --> 07:46.841
"How's Lettie?"

07:46.841 --> 07:49.636
Okay. I'm gonna go.
Wait. Wait. Hang on.

07:49.636 --> 07:51.221
You and I need to
sit down with Nati.

07:51.221 --> 07:52.889
The marketing lady?
Yeah.
It's about the sangria.

07:52.889 --> 07:54.015
Carmen, I'm harvesting
in a week.

07:54.015 --> 07:55.350
I got my own grapes
to worry about.

07:55.350 --> 07:56.851
I can't be thinking
about the sangria right now.

07:56.851 --> 07:59.187
Ah, but you don't mind
cashing the checks, do you?

07:59.187 --> 08:01.272
Okay. Fine. Whatever.
Set it up.

08:01.272 --> 08:03.358
I already did.
2:00 p. m. at her office.

08:03.358 --> 08:06.653
Ooh! Nati!

08:06.653 --> 08:08.321
Someone was at an early
marketing meeting.

08:08.321 --> 08:10.824
Okay.
Wait.
You hooked up with Nati?

08:10.824 --> 08:12.367
I was talking to her
at the Tastemaker event.

08:12.367 --> 08:13.868
She's hot!
I feel like maybe --

08:13.868 --> 08:15.745
[ Speaks Spanish ]

08:17.664 --> 08:18.873
What do you mean by that?

08:18.873 --> 08:20.709
Antonio:
Figure it out.

08:20.709 --> 08:22.877
[ Grumbles ]

08:22.877 --> 08:24.504
Ohh.

08:24.504 --> 08:26.256
Antonio: There you are.

08:26.256 --> 08:28.800
You get
that rotation schedule I sent?

08:28.800 --> 08:31.720
Yeah. There's a few things
to consider.

08:31.720 --> 08:33.888
Mostly having the Zin so close
to the water source.

08:33.888 --> 08:35.598
But I'll e-mail you
my concerns.

08:35.598 --> 08:40.228
Or we can sit down and talk
about it, tonight, with food.

08:40.228 --> 08:41.771
What's that called again?

08:43.273 --> 08:45.108
You want to talk
about the harvest

08:45.108 --> 08:46.943
or next year's planting?

08:46.943 --> 08:48.778
That's my job.

08:48.778 --> 08:51.197
Otherwise, I'd prefer
not to hear from you.

08:51.197 --> 08:52.824
This is about the night
of Joe's award.

08:52.824 --> 08:54.576
No.

08:54.576 --> 08:57.412
It's about me realizing
that the Antonio that I knew...

08:57.412 --> 08:59.497
that I was
in love with...

08:59.497 --> 09:01.958
he's not coming back
to Sonoma.

09:05.003 --> 09:09.257
♪♪

09:09.257 --> 09:10.467
[ Knock on door ]

09:10.467 --> 09:12.177
Come in!

09:12.177 --> 09:14.888
Joe found out.

09:14.888 --> 09:17.432
He knows the bones
are his father's.

09:19.434 --> 09:20.769
[ Shuddered breath ]

09:25.148 --> 09:27.108
My father always had
some scheme going.

09:27.108 --> 09:29.652
Talk to the old-timers.
Someone must know something.

09:29.652 --> 09:31.321
Gonzo?
And Marta.

09:31.321 --> 09:33.073
Start with her.
She knows things.

09:33.073 --> 09:36.242
And, more importantly, I can
trust her to be discreet.

09:36.242 --> 09:38.620
We harvest in a week. You think
we should focus on that?

09:38.620 --> 09:41.831
I'm sorry. This is
a little emotional for me.

09:41.831 --> 09:43.333
What's the problem, Apá?

09:43.333 --> 09:45.293
We're used to pushing
our emotions down, aren't we?

09:52.383 --> 09:54.761
Okay. What is this?
What's going on?

09:54.761 --> 09:57.639
Nothing. It's like you told me
on the day that I left.

09:57.639 --> 10:00.683
Mind over matter.
"You'll forget him soon enough."

10:00.683 --> 10:04.312
Your leaving is the biggest
regret of my life.

10:04.312 --> 10:06.523
I'll apologize as many times
as you need to hear it.

10:06.523 --> 10:08.191
Why would you apologize?

10:08.191 --> 10:10.819
I'm grateful.
You made me who I am.

10:10.819 --> 10:12.570
Whenever I question
whether I have the strength

10:12.570 --> 10:15.406
to see a task through,
I think of you.

10:15.406 --> 10:17.450
"You'll forget him
soon enough."

10:17.450 --> 10:23.581
♪♪

10:23.581 --> 10:26.000
I never settled things
with my father.

10:26.000 --> 10:28.086
I won't make that mistake
with you.

10:28.086 --> 10:31.673
Please, Antonio.
Can you ever forgive me?

10:33.424 --> 10:35.009
[ Door opens ]

10:37.637 --> 10:39.347
Where is everybody?

10:39.347 --> 10:41.015
I rented the gym
for the morning.

10:41.015 --> 10:43.184
You said if I ever needed
a sparring partner...

10:43.184 --> 10:44.769
This is about
the other night.

10:49.607 --> 10:51.651
You think
I can't take you?

10:51.651 --> 10:52.986
I think you can try.

10:54.237 --> 10:55.738
♪ I keep crossing the line ♪

10:55.738 --> 10:56.906
[ Grunts, laughs ]

10:56.906 --> 10:58.867
Paid leave.
Gotta cap it at 10 days.

10:58.867 --> 11:01.244
We're not moving off 15.
State pays supplemental.

11:01.244 --> 11:03.079
Plus, that's more
than any California grower.

11:03.079 --> 11:05.248
[ Both grunt ]

11:05.248 --> 11:08.209
I've got a cramp!
[ Grunts ]

11:08.209 --> 11:09.544
[ Chuckling ] What?

11:09.544 --> 11:11.129
♪♪

11:11.129 --> 11:13.840
Come here.
Yeah.

11:13.840 --> 11:17.093
I guess I deserve this for the
way I behaved the other night.

11:17.093 --> 11:19.721
You didn't just embarrass me.
You undermined me.

11:19.721 --> 11:22.223
It's not gonna happen again.
Are we clear?

11:23.600 --> 11:24.893
Crystal.
Okay.

11:26.811 --> 11:28.688
So...
[ Clears throat ]

11:28.688 --> 11:30.398
I think that's about
all the punishment

11:30.398 --> 11:32.984
my fragile male ego
can take for the day.

11:32.984 --> 11:37.655
We do still have that deal
to negotiate.

11:37.655 --> 11:40.200
Maybe over dinner?
Sure.

11:40.200 --> 11:42.619
Yeah, a friend of mine
was telling me about
this great steakhouse.

11:42.619 --> 11:43.953
Oh. No, no, no.
[ Chuckles ]

11:43.953 --> 11:45.955
I can't trust you
in public.

11:45.955 --> 11:48.208
Not after that stunt
you pulled.

11:48.208 --> 11:50.460
Sandoval Estate.

11:50.460 --> 11:51.961
8:00 p. m.

11:51.961 --> 11:53.296
Scene of the crime?

11:53.296 --> 11:55.256
See if you can behave
this time.

11:56.591 --> 11:59.802
I thought
it would haunt me.

11:59.802 --> 12:03.640
I thought I'd think about it
all the time, but I don't.

12:03.640 --> 12:05.892
You fill up your days
with...

12:05.892 --> 12:10.146
projects and kids
and...life.

12:12.148 --> 12:15.360
Lettie.

12:15.360 --> 12:17.320
I know we've had our differences
over the years.

12:17.320 --> 12:18.821
Well, that's one way
to put it.

12:18.821 --> 12:23.159
But I am saying this
as the friend I used to be.

12:23.159 --> 12:26.412
I know we promised to take
this secret to our graves,

12:26.412 --> 12:29.499
but you have kept it
long enough.

12:29.499 --> 12:30.667
I can't tell him.

12:30.667 --> 12:31.918
You have to tell him.

12:31.918 --> 12:33.253
I'll lose him.

12:33.253 --> 12:34.629
Maybe he'll understand.

12:34.629 --> 12:35.964
It's Joe.

12:35.964 --> 12:37.423
Well...

12:37.423 --> 12:38.883
Take him to a restaurant.

12:38.883 --> 12:41.302
Somewhere he won't
make a scene.

12:41.302 --> 12:43.179
Somewhere
he has to listen.

12:43.179 --> 12:46.307
Aren't you afraid of him
finding out the truth?

12:46.307 --> 12:48.309
Afraid of what?
That he won't love me anymore?

12:48.309 --> 12:50.311
Honey,
that ship has sailed.

12:52.397 --> 12:54.732
Margaret.

12:54.732 --> 12:57.026
I never asked him
to leave you.

12:58.528 --> 13:02.198
You should tell him, before
he finds out some other way.

13:02.198 --> 13:04.367
[ Cellphone buzzing ]

13:04.367 --> 13:06.869
Oh. I'm so sorry.
I have to take this.

13:06.869 --> 13:08.288
No, no, no.

13:08.288 --> 13:09.706
[ Click ]

13:09.706 --> 13:11.582
Hello.
This is Margaret.

13:11.582 --> 13:14.752
Antonio:
The bones in the vineyard,
they're Joe's father's.

13:14.752 --> 13:16.337
I heard.

13:16.337 --> 13:17.797
From who?

13:17.797 --> 13:19.507
I'm so sorry.
I can't talk right now.

13:19.507 --> 13:21.551
I have an old friend
visiting.

13:21.551 --> 13:22.677
Lettie?

13:22.677 --> 13:24.095
Correct!

13:24.095 --> 13:25.471
Well, did she mention
that your plan

13:25.471 --> 13:27.348
to burn down her marriage
is busted?

13:27.348 --> 13:28.891
Father Ramos left Sonoma.

13:28.891 --> 13:30.351
That's okay.

13:30.351 --> 13:33.646
I think another opportunity
just presented itself.

13:33.646 --> 13:36.024
[ Dinging ]

13:36.024 --> 13:39.110
[ Sighs ]

13:39.110 --> 13:41.029
[ Water running ]

13:44.532 --> 13:46.159
[ Water shuts off ]

13:54.584 --> 13:56.377
[ Sighs ]

14:04.594 --> 14:06.095
Sí.
[ Sniffles ]

14:36.167 --> 14:37.960
I love you.

14:43.132 --> 14:45.134
[ Sobbing ]

15:32.265 --> 15:35.434
[ Sobbing ]

15:57.540 --> 15:59.417
[ Indistinct conversation ]

16:05.756 --> 16:07.258
No, Billy.

16:24.358 --> 16:26.027
Hey.

16:28.905 --> 16:37.997
♪♪

16:37.997 --> 16:39.665
[ Truck door closes ]

16:39.665 --> 16:43.628
♪♪

16:43.628 --> 16:45.504
¿Qué pasó, Carlito?

16:56.390 --> 17:02.104
♪♪

17:02.104 --> 17:05.149
[ Music playing softly ]

17:05.149 --> 17:06.359
[ Doorbell rings ]

17:06.359 --> 17:07.610
iLa puerta!

17:07.610 --> 17:09.528
Can somebody
grab that?!

17:10.655 --> 17:11.989
[ Door closes ]

17:11.989 --> 17:14.951
Well, look who I found
picketing in the driveway.

17:14.951 --> 17:16.285
Hola.
Hi.

17:16.285 --> 17:18.371
I was too scared to bring wine
to the Sandoval house,

17:18.371 --> 17:20.122
so I hope tequila works.

17:20.122 --> 17:22.458
Lettie: [ Chuckles ]
This one's scared.

17:23.709 --> 17:25.253
[ Laughs ]

17:25.253 --> 17:27.838
See, in the spirit of our
collaborative negotiation,

17:27.838 --> 17:29.966
we could cook dinner
together.

17:29.966 --> 17:33.344
Unless a man of the people like
you needs someone to serve him.

17:33.344 --> 17:35.930
I gotta go. Joe and I
are going into town.

17:35.930 --> 17:37.765
Make yourself
at home.

17:37.765 --> 17:39.559
Hope you don't mind.
I started without you.

17:39.559 --> 17:41.018
Caldo de Res.
You want to taste it?

17:41.018 --> 17:42.770
Ah, yes. Love to.

17:44.522 --> 17:46.274
Watch out. It's hot.

17:46.274 --> 17:49.819
♪♪

17:49.819 --> 17:51.862
Wow.
That's really good.

17:51.862 --> 17:53.197
Huh?

17:53.197 --> 17:55.658
Yeah, I'm Cuban,
so it reminds me of, uh...

17:55.658 --> 17:57.952
[ Clears throat ]

17:57.952 --> 17:59.996
Pepper too much?

17:59.996 --> 18:01.247
You okay?

18:04.375 --> 18:06.627
Good. So, I think
the salary increases

18:06.627 --> 18:08.504
that we're offering
are more than generous,

18:08.504 --> 18:10.631
given the harvest
we had last year.

18:10.631 --> 18:12.466
I mean, but if you want us
to go higher,

18:12.466 --> 18:15.052
you could always offer us
something in return.

18:16.846 --> 18:18.180
Bread?

18:18.180 --> 18:20.016
She had to push the meeting.
Relax.

18:20.016 --> 18:21.642
You do know I harvest
in a week, right?

18:21.642 --> 18:23.144
Yeah, you might have
mentioned it.

18:23.144 --> 18:24.645
Listen.
Try not to be a hater.

18:24.645 --> 18:26.022
I'm not a hater.
You hate everything.

18:26.022 --> 18:27.356
I do not hate
everything.

18:27.356 --> 18:28.733
Remember that cooking class
that V got you for Christmas?

18:28.733 --> 18:30.943
I hated that class.
Because you hate everything.

18:30.943 --> 18:34.071
I hated that guy, too.
Chef Patrick? Not a good guy.

18:34.071 --> 18:35.740
Try not to hate Nati,
okay?

18:35.740 --> 18:38.492
She's got good ideas,
and it's important to me.

18:40.077 --> 18:43.372
Hey. Uh, so sorry
to keep you guys waiting.

18:43.372 --> 18:45.625
It's okay.
He, uh, needed a pep talk.

18:45.625 --> 18:48.377
Right. Mateo.

18:48.377 --> 18:51.756
So, I hear Gitana
needs a media push.

18:51.756 --> 18:53.007
Here's what I'm thinking.

18:53.007 --> 18:55.343
15-second viral spot videos
that we microtarget

18:55.343 --> 18:58.679
to the high-income,
young-adult demographic.

18:58.679 --> 19:00.056
How does that sound?

19:00.056 --> 19:02.850
"Viral spot" sounds like a trip
to the dermatologist.

19:02.850 --> 19:04.185
Mm-kay.

19:04.185 --> 19:06.604
Uh, Carmen told me
that Gitana's

19:06.604 --> 19:09.023
not exactly filling
your passion bucket.

19:09.023 --> 19:10.775
She did?

19:10.775 --> 19:13.110
Look, if we do this right,
within a year,

19:13.110 --> 19:14.362
you will be on the menu

19:14.362 --> 19:16.572
of every high-end restaurant
in North America.

19:16.572 --> 19:18.741
I mean, in two years, we'll have
you in the supermarkets and --

19:18.741 --> 19:20.618
Supermarkets?
I-I'm sorry.

19:20.618 --> 19:22.036
You don't get it.
She doesn't get it.

19:22.036 --> 19:24.955
Mm. I know.
Success is the worst.

19:24.955 --> 19:27.291
Uh, sorry. Is there something
wrong with supermarkets?

19:29.168 --> 19:30.503
Are you ashamed
of your product?

19:30.503 --> 19:33.381
No. It's nuanced.
It's fruity.

19:33.381 --> 19:35.174
It has accents
of pepper.

19:35.174 --> 19:37.927
Gitana is amazing
for a sangria.
Gitana isn't the problem.

19:37.927 --> 19:41.430
It's just not a Pinot
or a Chardonnay.

19:41.430 --> 19:44.183
Okay. Fine. I am a wine snob.
Are you happy?

19:44.183 --> 19:46.394
Do I look happy?
You're embarrassing me.

19:46.394 --> 19:49.438
So you two don't agree on...
anything?

19:50.523 --> 19:52.608
But you agree on Gitana?

19:52.608 --> 19:54.402
I was about to show you guys
a bunch of pictures

19:54.402 --> 19:56.987
of half-naked supermodels
drinking sangria, but...

19:56.987 --> 19:59.573
You were?
Yeah, but we are
scratching that idea.

19:59.573 --> 20:00.783
We are?
Yeah.

20:00.783 --> 20:03.786
I have a whole new concept.
You two.

20:03.786 --> 20:06.622
Sweet and sour.
City versus country.

20:06.622 --> 20:08.624
Heels versus work boots.

20:08.624 --> 20:10.876
Gitana is
for everybody.

20:10.876 --> 20:13.254
Uh...

20:13.254 --> 20:14.922
It's actually
not bad.

20:16.632 --> 20:18.884
Look.
Am I sweet or sour?

20:18.884 --> 20:20.761
Take a guess, buddy.

20:22.430 --> 20:26.100
[ Indistinct conversations ]

20:26.100 --> 20:29.437
Querido, we have a dinner
reservation in 45 minutes.

20:29.437 --> 20:32.440
Sorry, mi amor, I'm swamped.
I have to cancel.

20:32.440 --> 20:35.484
Joe, I told you. I have
something important to discuss.

20:35.484 --> 20:37.695
Is it more important
than the harvest?

20:37.695 --> 20:40.948
More important than finding out
who killed my father?

20:40.948 --> 20:46.162
♪♪

20:46.162 --> 20:47.663
What is Marta
doing here?

20:47.663 --> 20:51.959
She's been the eyes and ears
of Heritage House for 35 years.

20:51.959 --> 20:53.461
She must know something.

20:53.461 --> 20:55.796
♪♪

21:02.344 --> 21:08.934
♪♪

21:08.934 --> 21:10.603
Do you know
what this is?

21:10.603 --> 21:12.646
Antonio told me.

21:14.023 --> 21:16.692
Any idea who wanted
my father dead?

21:16.692 --> 21:20.863
You forget that
I never met your father.

21:20.863 --> 21:24.950
I remember Billy told me
that he was a drunk.

21:24.950 --> 21:26.911
I was living
in the big house.

21:26.911 --> 21:28.788
I wasn't up
on all the gossip.

21:28.788 --> 21:32.166
Marta. How long
have we known each other?

21:32.166 --> 21:33.834
You must know something.

21:33.834 --> 21:37.087
Whoever buried Manuel
knew how to keep a secret.

21:37.087 --> 21:39.507
How can no one
know anything?

21:39.507 --> 21:42.426
A man is killed
and buried here,

21:42.426 --> 21:44.595
and no one knows
a single thing about it?!

21:44.595 --> 21:47.014
Apá.
Marta, who did this?

21:47.014 --> 21:48.474
Who?!

21:48.474 --> 21:50.559
Apá,
she said she doesn't know.

21:52.686 --> 21:54.313
Lettie,
take him to dinner.

21:54.313 --> 21:57.566
I'm not going to dinner.
I have a harvest next week.

21:57.566 --> 22:00.736
♪♪

22:00.736 --> 22:02.738
I gotta go. I...

22:04.782 --> 22:07.409
I'm gonna see if one
of the ladies at the club

22:07.409 --> 22:08.911
is free for dinner.

22:18.629 --> 22:21.507
You just lied
to my father.

22:21.507 --> 22:23.551
I sincerely hope
you don't do the same to me.

22:35.020 --> 22:37.439
I remember one night,
when I was 8.

22:37.439 --> 22:39.316
Joe and Margaret
were fighting.

22:39.316 --> 22:41.485
And the next morning,
when I woke up,

22:41.485 --> 22:43.445
I asked you
where my mom was.

22:43.445 --> 22:47.199
And you sat
at the edge of my bed.

22:47.199 --> 22:50.619
And before you answered, you
started rubbing this bracelet.

22:50.619 --> 22:52.705
You told me a story
about how Margaret went to visit

22:52.705 --> 22:58.002
her brother and that she'd
be back before my birthday.

22:58.002 --> 23:00.880
My birthday came and went.

23:00.880 --> 23:03.090
And so did the next 20.

23:03.090 --> 23:04.592
'Tonio...

23:04.592 --> 23:06.594
You knew
they filed for divorce.

23:08.971 --> 23:11.098
Yet you lied for my sake.

23:12.349 --> 23:14.393
You were different then.

23:16.812 --> 23:18.564
Out of all the children,
you were my favorite.

23:18.564 --> 23:19.648
[ Chuckles ]

23:19.648 --> 23:22.276
I knew your secret
before you did,

23:22.276 --> 23:25.613
and I loved you
even more for it.

23:25.613 --> 23:27.823
You were fearless.

23:27.823 --> 23:30.826
Not just because of
who you loved

23:30.826 --> 23:33.037
but how you loved --

23:33.037 --> 23:37.499
with your whole heart,
never afraid of being hurt.

23:38.959 --> 23:41.879
Until Joe sent you away.

23:41.879 --> 23:45.132
And then this hardness
took over.

23:45.132 --> 23:48.636
Antonio, he loves you.

23:50.763 --> 23:56.101
The way he and I grew up,
it was a sin.

23:56.101 --> 24:00.564
People were beaten,
murdered.

24:00.564 --> 24:04.944
He wasn't trying to protect
the family from you.

24:04.944 --> 24:08.489
He was trying to protect you
from the world.

24:08.489 --> 24:11.158
I know it doesn't feel
that way...

24:11.158 --> 24:12.868
but it's true.

24:16.205 --> 24:18.999
You know how this business
will look if this gets out?

24:18.999 --> 24:21.168
They will crucify
my father.

24:21.168 --> 24:22.878
Don't let them, Antonio.

24:22.878 --> 24:25.881
You have to protect him.

24:25.881 --> 24:27.174
The same way
he protected you.

24:27.174 --> 24:28.801
I can't.

24:28.801 --> 24:31.679
Not unless I know what
I'm protecting him from.

24:31.679 --> 24:33.180
Antonio.

24:36.517 --> 24:37.977
Please.

24:40.354 --> 24:42.856
Marta told me.

24:46.360 --> 24:48.612
I know it was you and Lettie
who killed my grandfather.

24:50.906 --> 24:53.867
It's torturing Joe.

24:53.867 --> 24:55.536
You have to tell him.

24:56.662 --> 24:58.789
I thought you enjoyed
torturing Joe.

24:58.789 --> 25:01.166
And I thought you
wanted to destroy his
and Lettie's marriage.

25:01.166 --> 25:04.253
She saved my life,
Antonio.

25:04.253 --> 25:06.422
What happened that night
is not a chess piece.

25:06.422 --> 25:07.756
But Lettie is?

25:07.756 --> 25:09.758
You seem perfectly fine
letting her tell him.

25:09.758 --> 25:11.301
She's his wife.

25:11.301 --> 25:13.721
And apparently she wants it
to stay that way.

25:13.721 --> 25:17.099
Joe lit into Marta.
Lettie got spooked.

25:17.099 --> 25:19.309
She won't be confessing
anytime soon.

25:21.228 --> 25:23.063
He deserves to know.

25:23.063 --> 25:24.982
[ Sighs ]

25:24.982 --> 25:28.444
All these years...

25:28.444 --> 25:30.487
you still don't want
to break his heart.

25:33.949 --> 25:35.743
Good night, Antonio.

25:35.743 --> 25:45.127
♪♪

25:45.127 --> 25:47.296
[ Indistinct conversations ]

25:54.887 --> 25:57.473
Sandoval!

26:11.862 --> 26:13.822
[ Laughs ]

26:50.984 --> 26:52.694
Sí.

26:59.827 --> 27:02.955
It's the first meal I've cooked
in two years.

27:02.955 --> 27:05.082
As depressing
as that sounds.

27:05.082 --> 27:07.167
You know, I don't think
I'd mind all the travel.

27:07.167 --> 27:08.502
I love hotels.

27:08.502 --> 27:11.213
Labor lawyers don't exactly
stay at the Honeycroft.

27:11.213 --> 27:13.215
But this life
has its upsides.

27:13.215 --> 27:16.677
For instance, you don't have to
be a firsthand witness

27:16.677 --> 27:19.346
to your marriages
falling apart.

27:19.346 --> 27:21.348
Does it get any easier
the second time?

27:21.348 --> 27:23.475
Like to make a joke right here,
but no.

27:23.475 --> 27:26.478
It's the worst.
Um...

27:26.478 --> 27:27.855
Just feels...

27:27.855 --> 27:30.232
Like failure?

27:30.232 --> 27:31.775
Yeah.

27:33.986 --> 27:36.947
You know, I don't think I've
ever failed at anything before.

27:36.947 --> 27:38.574
I know that sounds
conceited and --

27:38.574 --> 27:42.411
It doesn't.
I -- I've met you.

27:42.411 --> 27:46.081
Of all the things
to fail at.

27:46.081 --> 27:49.626
Don't get me wrong. It's not
like I'm grieving that weasel.

27:49.626 --> 27:52.546
You're grieving the idea that
life is under your control.

27:52.546 --> 27:54.089
But it's not.

27:55.716 --> 27:56.884
10 days paid leave.

27:59.261 --> 28:00.637
Man,
you are relentless.

28:00.637 --> 28:02.848
[ Both chuckle ]

28:04.016 --> 28:05.851
Okay. Fine.
It's a deal.

28:05.851 --> 28:07.728
If...

28:07.728 --> 28:11.023
Heritage House agrees to fund
the ESL program again.

28:13.191 --> 28:16.403
♪♪

28:16.403 --> 28:18.488
Congratulations.

28:18.488 --> 28:20.532
[ Glasses clink ]

28:20.532 --> 28:22.784
How should we celebrate?

28:22.784 --> 28:26.079
♪ Don't act so special ♪

28:26.079 --> 28:27.456
Grand Reserva.

28:27.456 --> 28:29.374
Finest Heritage House
has to offer.

28:29.374 --> 28:31.418
♪ It's not for you ♪

28:31.418 --> 28:33.545
♪ Forget about it ♪

28:33.545 --> 28:35.797
♪ You made this mess ♪

28:35.797 --> 28:39.301
♪ I'll knock at your door ♪

28:39.301 --> 28:41.261
♪ Don't you ignore ♪

28:41.261 --> 28:43.221
♪ Or forget about it ♪

28:43.221 --> 28:44.973
♪ Every night ♪

28:44.973 --> 28:48.435
♪ Got you running in circles,
I know ♪

28:48.435 --> 28:50.062
♪ Touchin' me ♪

28:50.062 --> 28:53.649
♪ Get your paws
off my Dolce cologne ♪

28:53.649 --> 28:55.275
♪ Back it up ♪

28:55.275 --> 28:58.695
♪ Off my throne
'cause you know you wanna ♪

28:58.695 --> 29:00.364
♪ Make me ♪

29:00.364 --> 29:03.617
♪ Walk away
and forget about it ♪

29:08.789 --> 29:11.625
It's sweet
but not too sweet.

29:11.625 --> 29:14.336
Like --
I don't know -- me.

29:17.798 --> 29:18.840
Uh...

29:18.840 --> 29:20.550
Cut! Mnh!

29:20.550 --> 29:22.135
I'm sorry. I'm --
I'm -- I'm so sorry.

29:22.135 --> 29:23.261
I can't do this.
Mateo.

29:23.261 --> 29:24.513
I'm so sorry.
I can't do this, Carmen.

29:24.513 --> 29:25.973
I said I don't want this
traced back to me,

29:25.973 --> 29:27.641
and now, what,
I'm in a freakin' commercial?

29:27.641 --> 29:28.809
With makeup on my face?

29:28.809 --> 29:30.227
Okay. Just --
[ Stammers ]

29:30.227 --> 29:31.853
No one is going to
recognize you.

29:31.853 --> 29:33.939
They're just gonna think
you're an unemployed actor.

29:33.939 --> 29:35.983
God knows
he dresses like one.
I heard that.

29:35.983 --> 29:38.527
Mateo, please.
Just do it for me.

29:39.820 --> 29:42.072
Alright. Here we go.
Take number...

29:42.072 --> 29:44.199
I don't even know
because I lost count.

29:44.199 --> 29:47.327
[ Clears throat ]
Alright. And...action.

29:48.370 --> 29:49.454
Cut.

29:49.454 --> 29:50.789
Oh, my God.
Just one more thing.

29:50.789 --> 29:52.249
Could you just put this down
a little bit?

29:52.249 --> 29:53.625
He doesn't need more light
on his face.

29:53.625 --> 29:54.960
He's already haggard
as it is.

29:54.960 --> 29:57.254
And you --
you know what you're...?

29:57.254 --> 29:58.839
"Cinema verite."
Like you wanted.

29:58.839 --> 30:00.966
I'm sorry. Who's directing
this thing again?

30:00.966 --> 30:02.843
-Sorry. You're good.
-Yeah?

30:02.843 --> 30:04.511
Yeah.
Okay.
If we're good, we're good.

30:04.511 --> 30:06.138
And...action!

30:07.639 --> 30:09.266
You were incredible.

30:10.684 --> 30:11.893
I know.

30:11.893 --> 30:13.353
[ Both laugh ]

30:13.353 --> 30:15.355
Hey.
It was a team effort.

30:15.355 --> 30:16.898
You, me, Nati.

30:16.898 --> 30:19.484
No. You have such an amazing
vision for this sangria, Carmen,

30:19.484 --> 30:21.236
but it's not mine.

30:21.236 --> 30:22.529
It's all you.

30:22.529 --> 30:23.822
I want you
to have the company.

30:23.822 --> 30:25.824
-Yeah. In the back.
-Oh, okay.

30:25.824 --> 30:28.326
What are you talking about?
No, don't get me wrong.

30:28.326 --> 30:29.578
I've had a blast
working with you.

30:29.578 --> 30:31.246
And you're right --
I don't mind cashing the checks,

30:31.246 --> 30:34.332
but at the end of the day,
it's not about the money for me.

30:34.332 --> 30:37.836
Gitana is not my passion.
It's yours.

30:37.836 --> 30:40.213
And it's so inspiring
to see.

30:42.549 --> 30:44.009
Ohh. [ Chuckles ]

30:44.009 --> 30:46.553
[ Laughs ]
Oh!

30:48.889 --> 30:50.599
Thank you.

30:50.599 --> 30:52.559
But I'm not gonna
take your charity.

30:52.559 --> 30:54.227
I'll buy you out.

30:54.227 --> 30:56.271
Oh, thank God.
I was hoping you'd say that.

30:56.271 --> 30:57.731
[ Both laugh ]

30:57.731 --> 31:00.317
I've gotta pay rent.
Yeah.

31:00.317 --> 31:02.194
Plus, I don't know --
I got a really, really

31:02.194 --> 31:04.196
good feeling
about this year's harvest.
Yeah?

31:04.196 --> 31:06.907
Halfway decent shot of getting
into Wine Snob magazine.

31:06.907 --> 31:08.617
[ Both laugh ]

31:09.659 --> 31:11.411
Rosa:
Yes. Okay. Thank you.

31:11.411 --> 31:13.121
[ Receiver hangs up ]

31:16.708 --> 31:19.002
Ay. Rosa!

31:22.089 --> 31:23.757
Junior college.

31:40.482 --> 31:42.484
Ay, ay, Billy!

31:43.902 --> 31:45.821
-Okay.
-[ Speaks Spanish ]

31:48.198 --> 31:49.991
No, Lettie.

31:51.618 --> 31:53.120
No.

31:53.120 --> 31:54.496
Sí.

32:08.093 --> 32:12.264
♪♪

32:12.264 --> 32:13.849
Joe.

32:34.870 --> 32:39.207
[ Speaks Spanish ]

32:41.626 --> 32:43.670
♪♪

32:43.670 --> 32:45.005
[ Crow caws ]

32:45.005 --> 32:54.181
♪♪

32:54.181 --> 33:03.440
♪♪

33:03.440 --> 33:12.616
♪♪

33:57.577 --> 34:07.003
♪♪

34:07.003 --> 34:16.471
♪♪

34:16.471 --> 34:25.981
♪♪

34:25.981 --> 34:27.899
Margaret: I should have
told you years ago,

34:27.899 --> 34:30.026
but I promised Lettie
that I wouldn't.

34:30.026 --> 34:32.988
Then when I heard the bones
had been found...

34:34.155 --> 34:36.449
I can't keep the truth
from you any longer.

34:36.449 --> 34:38.076
I'm so sorry, Joe.

34:43.164 --> 34:44.416
Why didn't you tell me?

34:44.416 --> 34:46.793
I tried. Last night.

34:46.793 --> 34:48.336
Last night?!

34:48.336 --> 34:49.796
What about
the last 30 years?!

34:49.796 --> 34:50.964
Joe, she was
only trying to --

34:50.964 --> 34:52.757
Trying to protect you.
Fine!

34:52.757 --> 34:55.010
And my father was a
son of a bitch who deserved it.

34:55.010 --> 34:57.679
That's not the point.

34:59.014 --> 35:02.809
You let me believe
that I drove him away.

35:02.809 --> 35:06.479
You saw that pain,
and you said nothing.

35:06.479 --> 35:10.692
And I will regret that
for the rest of my life, Joe.

35:10.692 --> 35:13.862
But I do not regret
what I did.

35:13.862 --> 35:17.657
But if it happened again,
to save my friend,

35:17.657 --> 35:20.535
I would do the same thing
in a heartbeat.

35:22.370 --> 35:24.039
I think
you should leave.

35:24.039 --> 35:27.292
♪♪

35:27.292 --> 35:30.462
[ Shuddered breathing ]

35:40.221 --> 35:42.015
[ Bird calling ]

35:53.985 --> 35:55.487
Yes.

36:07.957 --> 36:15.799
♪♪

36:15.799 --> 36:23.682
♪♪

36:31.940 --> 36:37.112
♪♪

36:37.112 --> 36:42.283
♪♪

36:42.283 --> 36:45.412
[ Car door opens, closes ]

36:46.079 --> 36:47.789
You okay?

36:47.789 --> 36:49.499
[ Engine starts ]

36:49.499 --> 36:55.588
♪♪

36:55.588 --> 37:01.845
♪♪

37:01.845 --> 37:04.097
It's a win-win.
Our workers are happy,

37:04.097 --> 37:07.517
and our stock will go up 5%
when we announce.

37:07.517 --> 37:10.353
Jittery shareholders
love labor peace.

37:10.353 --> 37:13.815
You reinstituted
the ESL program.

37:13.815 --> 37:16.067
I know that was important
to Lettie.

37:16.067 --> 37:18.445
Thought maybe you could
tell her yourself.

37:19.779 --> 37:22.323
Important to Lettie.

37:22.323 --> 37:23.616
Apá?

37:26.536 --> 37:28.955
What the hell
are you doing?

37:28.955 --> 37:30.540
I didn't want a win-win.

37:30.540 --> 37:32.834
Just a win.
For Heritage House.

37:32.834 --> 37:34.627
You gave me the authority
to make a deal.

37:34.627 --> 37:35.920
I gave them my word!

37:35.920 --> 37:37.547
I'm reopening
negotiations.

37:37.547 --> 37:40.133
Oh, you don't want a win
for Heritage House.

37:40.133 --> 37:42.927
You just wanted a win
for Joe Sandoval. For you.

37:42.927 --> 37:45.388
I am Heritage House!

37:48.308 --> 37:49.559
[ Indistinct conversation ]

37:49.559 --> 37:51.895
What's this I hear
about not working?!

37:51.895 --> 37:54.981
We start harvesting today.
I need everyone out there.

37:57.734 --> 37:59.360
Well, did you hear
what I just said?

37:59.360 --> 38:01.029
Get to work!

38:01.029 --> 38:02.614
Gonzo.

38:14.000 --> 38:15.752
♪♪

38:15.752 --> 38:18.213
[ Workers murmuring ]

38:18.213 --> 38:21.758
Oh, you have no idea
what you've done.

38:21.758 --> 38:24.427
This is a war now.

38:24.427 --> 38:27.680
[ Speaks Spanish ]

38:27.680 --> 38:31.684
Oh. Perdon. I forgot, uh,
you don't speak Spanish.

38:31.684 --> 38:33.645
Lettie...

38:33.645 --> 38:36.064
[ Speaks Spanish ]

38:38.233 --> 38:40.068
We like our chances.

38:46.157 --> 38:49.619
Fine. Fine.

38:49.619 --> 38:51.746
You think
I can't replace you?

38:51.746 --> 38:54.916
Do you know how many there are
just like you?!

38:54.916 --> 38:56.376
Busloads!

38:56.376 --> 38:59.045
You'll never work
at this vineyard again!

38:59.045 --> 39:02.173
♪♪

39:02.173 --> 39:04.342
Thanks so much
for dinner tonight, Mama.

39:04.342 --> 39:07.220
It's the least
I can do, right?

39:07.220 --> 39:10.139
Thank you
for letting me stay here.

39:10.139 --> 39:12.642
It's good practice for me
for when you're an abuela.

39:15.061 --> 39:16.729
Plus, you always used to
remind me how our culture

39:16.729 --> 39:18.815
takes care of their elders.
I'm not an elder.

39:18.815 --> 39:19.816
No?
No.

39:19.816 --> 39:21.109
At some point.
You're so bad.

39:21.109 --> 39:22.151
[ Knock on door ]

39:22.151 --> 39:23.903
Are you expecting someone?

39:28.116 --> 39:29.784
[ Door opens ]

39:29.784 --> 39:31.452
Mama!
Yeah?

39:31.452 --> 39:32.579
It's for you.

39:32.579 --> 39:33.788
[ Door closes ]

39:33.788 --> 39:35.373
Joe Sandoval.

39:39.752 --> 39:45.008
♪♪

39:45.008 --> 39:46.759
Rosa?

39:48.761 --> 39:50.930
[ Gasps ] Rosa!

39:50.930 --> 39:52.640
[ Laughs ]

39:52.640 --> 39:54.434
Ohh.

39:54.434 --> 40:00.523
♪♪

40:00.523 --> 40:02.233
[ Sighs ]

40:02.233 --> 40:04.235
We need to talk.

40:04.235 --> 40:05.445
Is this about work?

40:05.445 --> 40:06.738
No.

40:06.738 --> 40:08.156
Good night.

40:08.156 --> 40:10.033
I came to Sonoma
to take down my father

40:10.033 --> 40:11.868
and take control
over Heritage House.

40:13.828 --> 40:16.664
You know, for weeks,
I've been chasing down a ghost.

40:16.664 --> 40:20.335
A man named
Carlos Rincón.

40:20.335 --> 40:22.253
I had theories.

40:22.253 --> 40:25.006
Maybe it was someone shady
Joe was mixed up with or...

40:25.006 --> 40:28.468
maybe even someone
he killed.

40:28.468 --> 40:33.932
But every time that I got close,
I kept hitting a dead end.

40:33.932 --> 40:35.808
Until now.

40:35.808 --> 40:40.563
♪♪

40:40.563 --> 40:42.190
Marta gave me
this wallet.

40:42.190 --> 40:43.900
"Manuel Rincón."

40:43.900 --> 40:46.945
Joe's father.
The man whose bones you found.

40:51.240 --> 40:52.992
Then who's
Joe Sandoval?

40:52.992 --> 40:55.787
A math teacher in San Dimas.
He died in 1986.

40:55.787 --> 40:57.372
My father
came into this country

40:57.372 --> 41:01.084
and assumed the identity
of a dead man.

41:01.084 --> 41:05.254
That's the secret that Joe's
been keeping all these years.

41:05.254 --> 41:06.965
He didn't kill anyone.

41:06.965 --> 41:09.008
He's undocumented.

41:09.008 --> 41:11.135
What are you gonna do?

41:11.135 --> 41:14.514
You know, for years...

41:14.514 --> 41:16.975
my anger for Joe
consumed me.

41:18.935 --> 41:21.854
It kept me from loving
the people that loved me back.

41:21.854 --> 41:25.525
What will you do,
Antonio?

41:25.525 --> 41:27.026
Nothing.

41:29.862 --> 41:31.906
We take this
to our graves.

41:33.783 --> 41:35.785
Well, there you are.

41:35.785 --> 41:39.539
♪♪

41:39.539 --> 41:41.958
Margaret: Joe Sandoval
was a great man.

41:41.958 --> 41:45.169
I knew it from the moment
I met him.

41:45.169 --> 41:48.548
But let's face it --
he's changed.

41:48.548 --> 41:52.385
He is no longer capable
of running Heritage House.

41:52.385 --> 41:55.138
And that is why
I'm launching this takeover.

41:55.138 --> 41:59.058
It's why I invited you here
tonight.

41:59.058 --> 42:01.978
As a shareholder,
you have the power

42:01.978 --> 42:05.481
to shape the future
of Heritage House.

42:05.481 --> 42:09.360
And maybe...to save it.

42:10.653 --> 42:11.821
Let's talk.

42:16.534 --> 42:25.960
♪♪

42:25.960 --> 42:35.428
♪♪

42:35.428 --> 42:44.896
♪♪
